From 0ba806c48aeb5c98ff13885c96245c8949989649 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: David Bauer <mail@david-bauer.net>
Date: Thu, 12 Mar 2026 00:56:34 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] wifi: mt76: mt7915: set mt76 specific PS flag

mt76 tracks the PSM state of a sta internally with a wcid flag. TX to
such clients is skipped based on the presence of this flag.

This flag was not added to the PS state notify handler for MT7915 chips.
This can lead to inconsistent behavior and TX scheduling to STAs in
power save under the condition of a TX free event after a PS sleep
event.

Set the PS flag for the STA WCID to prevent this from happening. TX gets
skipped in presence of this flag.

Signed-off-by: David Bauer <mail@david-bauer.net>
